{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Etymology===
Late Old English ''[[werewulf]]'', probably from [[wer#Old English|wer]] ‘man’ + [[wulf#Old English|wulf]] ‘wolf’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ˈwɛ:wʊlf/, /ˈwɪəwʊlf/}} (''UK'')

===Noun===
{{en-noun|werewolves}}

# (''mythology'') A [[person]] who is [[transform]]ed into a [[wolf]] or a wolflike human when there is a [[full moon]].

====Synonyms====
*[[lycanthrope]]
*[[neurian]]
*[[wolfman]]

